<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/style.css">
  <style>
    .intro-container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 4rem auto;
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .intro-container h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      text-align: center;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }

    .intro-section {
      margin: 3rem 0;
      padding: 2rem;
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
      border-radius: 12px;
      border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
    }

    .intro-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
      color: #667eea;
    }

    .intro-section p {
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin: 1rem 0;
      opacity: 0.9;
    }

    .intro-section ul {
      margin: 1rem 0;
      padding-left: 1.5rem;
    }

    .intro-section li {
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .intro-actions {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 3rem;
    }

    .intro-btn {
      padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
      color: white;
      border: none;
      border-radius: 8px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    }

    .intro-btn:hover {
      transform: translateY(-2px);
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.4);
    }

    .intro-btn:active {
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    .skip-btn {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }

    .skip-btn:hover {
      background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
      box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="intro-container">
    <h1>How to Play Stringborn</h1>

    <div class="intro-section">
      <h2>1. Create Your Character</h2>
      <p>
        Every journey begins with a character. Choose your species, assign your stats,
        and customize your appearance. Your character is your avatar in the Stringborn universe.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Select from multiple species, each with unique traits</li>
        <li>Distribute stat points across Strength, Intelligence, Agility, Faith, and Tech</li>
        <li>You can create up to 3 characters per account</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
      <h2>2. Navigate the Universe</h2>
      <p>
        The Stringborn universe is vast and procedurally generated. Travel between zones,
        explore planets, and discover hidden anomalies.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the galactic map to plan your route</li>
        <li>Travel consumes time and resources</li>
        <li>Different zones offer different challenges and rewards</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
      <h2>3. Build & Create</h2>
      <p>
        The Asset Builder lets you create custom content that becomes part of the universe.
        Design ships, planets, items, and more.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Submit your creations for community voting</li>
        <li>Approved assets are added to the game</li>
        <li>Earn recognition and rewards for quality content</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
      <h2>4. Participate in Democracy</h2>
      <p>
        The Stringborn community votes on new content, features, and governance decisions.
        Your voice matters in shaping the future of the universe.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Vote on pending assets in the voting queue</li>
        <li>Participate in community discussions</li>
        <li>Help decide what content enters the game</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-actions">
      <button class="intro-btn" onclick="completeIntro()">
        Continue to Character Selection
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    async function completeIntro() {
      try {
        // Mark intro as completed
        const response = await fetch('/complete-intro', {
          method: 'POST',
          headers: {
            'Content-Type': 'application/json'
          }
        });

        const data = await response.json();

        if (response.ok) {
          // Check if user has any characters
          const charactersResponse = await fetch('/api/v1/characters');
          const charactersData = await charactersResponse.json();

          if (charactersData.characters && charactersData.characters.length > 0) {
            // User has characters, send to selection screen
            window.location.href = '/auth';
          } else {
            // No characters, send to creation
            window.location.href = '/characters/create';
          }
        } else {
          alert('Failed to complete intro. Please try again.');
        }
      } catch (err) {
        console.error('Error completing intro:', err);
        alert('An error occurred. Please try again.');
      }
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
